data.description: This condo with a GARAGE and STORAGE in Savoy Court is a fantastic opportunity for buyers looking for a great value. It even qualifies for the Welcome Home grant, offering $10,000 for closing costs. Additionally, you can take advantage of a lower-than-market interest rate and no PMI, saving you money in the long run.   Savoy Court is a well-maintained and gated condo community located in a quiet residential neighborhood. The condo itself is a freshly painted two-bedroom model, the largest in the building, and comes with its own private tandem garage for two cars that is OWNED and CONVEYS with the home plus a separate storage unit  in the building. The layout is ideal, with an open kitchen featuring expansive granite countertops and an island with stool seating, as well as a separate dining area. You'll also appreciate the extra storage, spacious bedrooms with new carpet, and large windows overlooking the courtyard. Plus, the unit includes an in-unit washer and dryer for added convenience.   The building offers a range of amenities for residents to enjoy. From a rooftop deck with a grill and stunning city views to a well-equipped fitness center and laundry room, you'll have everything you need right at your fingertips.   Location-wise, Savoy Court is conveniently situated near major highways like 295 and is close to new businesses in Congress Heights, the National Harbor, and a variety of entertainment options, restaurants, and retail. Congress Heights has become a hub for exciting sports events and concerts at the Entertainment and Sports Arena, hosting games for the Washington Mystics basketball team, Capital City Go-Go, and live music performances.   With its proximity to public transportation, including being just over a mile from the nearest metro station, and easy access to Capitol Hill and Alexandria, Virginia, this location offers unmatched accessibility.   If you're tired of renting and want to start building your own equity, don't miss out on the opportunity to purchase a home in Savoy Court. Please note that the home is owner-occupied, so please remove your shoes and provide at least one hour notice for showings. You can schedule a showing through Showing Time.   Thank you for showing interest in this property! *Universal Title is the preferred title company.
